{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_3","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-14-spotlight-memory-shortcuts.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Evolution Note — Spotlight Memory Shortcuts\n\n## Plan\n\n- path: `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- milestone: `Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer (complete)`\n- bounded target: add one minimal workflow-integration slice by surfacing Prompt / Rule / Memo quick-open shortcuts inside the selected-agent spotlight\n\n## Completed\n\n- Added a compact memory shortcut row to the selected-agent spotlight\n- Reused existing repo-file quick-open behavior so Prompt, Rule, and Memo sources are now reachable from the active-agent surface rather than only from the separate memory panel\n- Kept the slice limited to proximity and did not add editing or richer cross-card semantics\n\n## Failed or Deferred\n\n- Deferred deeper memory-agent linkage, editing flows, and richer memory behavior\n\n## Decisions\n\n- Treat spotlight-level memory shortcuts as the first bounded Task 3 step needed to bridge active agent context and memory artifacts\n- Move next to a Task 3 review instead of adding more memory behavior in the same pass\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n```text\nContinue the codex-loop from `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`. Stay on `task-plans/prompt-rule-memo-cards-task-plan.md` and do one Task 3 review focused on whether the new spotlight-level memory shortcuts are enough to close the first workflow-integration gap.\n```\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
